# BuildKit prefers `<dockerfile>.dockerignore` over the plain `.dockerignore`, so the traffic-runner
# image gets its own exclusion list. The root .dockerignore strips tests/, scripts/ and README.md —
# correct for the hardened runtime image, but those are exactly what this image is built to run.
# Keeping them separate means the production image stays lean without a conditional in either file.
.venv/
.git/
.github/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.idea/
.vscode/

__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
*.so

CLAUDE.md
LICENSE

.env
.env.*
*.log

Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml
